Oh. yes. Sorry.

261
00:15:39.896 --> 00:15:42.206
Victoria. er. Burkeman.

262
00:15:42.310 --> 00:15:43.413
[Mike] She attacked you?

263
00:15:43.517 --> 00:15:46.103
[Sophia] She did
lunge at me. and. erm...

264
00:15:48.310 --> 00:15:50.070
we struggled. we fell
to the ground. and I...

265
00:15:50.137 --> 00:15:52.793
I managed to back away
from her. but...

266
00:15:52.896 --> 00:15:54.586
she kept crawling towards me.

267
00:15:56.586 --> 00:15:57.665
[Mike] Was there any witnesses?

268
00:15:57.689 --> 00:15:59.068
Or CCTV?

269
00:16:03.206 --> 00:16:05.034
[sighs] There's nothing.

270
00:16:07.310 --> 00:16:08.620
She quoted the Bible.

271
00:16:09.689 --> 00:16:10.689
Which passage?

272
00:16:12.310 --> 00:16:15.689
Erm. it was. er...

273
00:16:17.344 --> 00:16:19.275
"Many... I am...

274
00:16:19.379 --> 00:16:21.241
My name is Legion
for we are many."

275
00:16:22.068 --> 00:16:23.137
That's right.

276
00:16:23.344 --> 00:16:24.620
[Mike] Mm.

277
00:16:25.241 --> 00:16:27.379
Mark chapter five. verse nine.

278
00:16:28.103 --> 00:16:31.344
It's a story about a man
who was possessed by demons.

279
00:16:32.482 --> 00:16:35.034
Jesus casts them out of him
and into pigs.

280
00:16:36.172 --> 00:16:37.344
[Jeanette] And then?

281
00:16:37.448 --> 00:16:38.724
[Mike] The pigs all drowned.

282
00:16:39.517 --> 00:16:41.862
Jesus'. erm. triumph over evil.

283
00:16:44.965 --> 00:16:49.241
Oh. Do you have any clue
what she could be referring to?

284
00:16:50.448 --> 00:16:52.034
No. Nothing.

285
00:16:52.137 --> 00:16:54.275
[Jeanette] Mm-hmm. Did she
say anything else at all?

286
00:16:54.379 --> 00:16:55.620
Yes. yes.

287
00:16:55.724 --> 00:16:56.965
She...

288
00:16:57.068 --> 00:17:00.551
Well. she kept saying.
"She's gone. She's gone."

289
00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:06.689
And she said.
"It's not just us. you know?"

290
00:17:08.586 --> 00:17:09.586
Then?

291
00:17:11.724 --> 00:17:13.931
And then she vanished. Er...

292
00:17:19.172 --> 00:17:21.206
We have reason
to believe that Victoria

293
00:17:21.310 --> 00:17:23.413
might be keeping
Mary Burkeman somewhere.

294
00:17:25.172 --> 00:17:26.212
Do you think she's capable

295
00:17:26.275 --> 00:17:28.448
of murdering her
own mother. Sophia?

296
00:17:32.344 --> 00:17:33.769
I think if she were
going to kill her

297
00:17:33.793 --> 00:17:35.965
she would have done it already.

298
00:17:36.586 --> 00:17:38.026
What was it like?
Their relationship?

299
00:17:38.724 --> 00:17:40.413
Between Victoria and her mother?

300
00:17:41.310 --> 00:17:42.344
Oh.

301
00:17:44.793 --> 00:17:46.172
Her mother was blind.

302
00:17:47.275 --> 00:17:49.827
Vacuous. self-centred. cruel.

303
00:17:52.068 --> 00:17:53.068
Mm.

304
00:17:57.758 --> 00:17:59.206
She wants you
to look for something.

305
00:18:05.275 --> 00:18:06.413
[bird caws]

306
00:18:09.344 --> 00:18:10.631
[female newsreader]
<i>The atmosphere in Bristol</i>

307
00:18:10.655 --> 00:18:12.379
<i>is heavy today
as grisly discoveries...</i>

308
00:18:12.482 --> 00:18:13.769
[male newsreader] <i>Several bodies
have been recovered</i>

309
00:18:13.793 --> 00:18:15.034
<i>from a working farm.</i>

310
00:18:15.137 --> 00:18:17.458
<i>And with the police yet to make
any arrests. it would appear...</i>

311
00:18:17.482 --> 00:18:20.413
[woman] <i>I feel scared to go out.
to be honest with you. yeah.</i>

312
00:18:20.517 --> 00:18:22.275
[male newsreader
continues indistinctly]

313
00:18:22.862 --> 00:18:24.320
[newsreader 3]
<i>The death toll has continued</i>

314
00:18:24.344 --> 00:18:25.724
<i>to rise considerably...</i>

315
00:18:26.275 --> 00:18:28.103
[newsreader
continues indistinctly]

316
00:18:34.965 --> 00:18:37.137
[Victoria whispering]
<i>For we are many.</i>

317
00:18:38.034 --> 00:18:40.344
[news continues indistinctly]

318
00:18:41.965 --> 00:18:43.320
[newsreader]
<i>Most recently. the area</i>

319
00:18:43.344 --> 00:18:45.068
<i>surrounding St Jordan's church</i>

320
00:18:45.172 --> 00:18:47.448
<i>has been cordoned off
as a crime scene</i>

321
00:18:47.551 --> 00:18:50.310
<i>following the discovery there
of a body earlier this morning.</i>

322
00:18:50.413 --> 00:18:51.838
<i>Police believe
the victim may have been</i>

323
00:18:51.862 --> 00:18:53.206
<i>hidden there for decades.</i>

324
00:18:53.310 --> 00:18:56.310
<i>Superintendent Verity Pound
dismissed concerns</i>

325
00:18:56.413 --> 00:18:58.206
<i>that it may be connected
to the recent spate</i>

326
00:18:58.310 --> 00:18:59.872
<i>-of murders in the city.</i>
-[Sophia sobs]

327
00:18:59.896 --> 00:19:01.482
[Verity] <i>We have
no reason to believe</i>

328
00:19:01.586 --> 00:19:03.482
<i>the two are connected.</i>

329
00:19:03.586 --> 00:19:05.965
<i>We have yet
to identify the victim</i>

330
00:19:06.068 --> 00:19:08.655
<i>and would urge the general
public to come forward</i>

331
00:19:08.758 --> 00:19:10.517
<i>if they have any information.</i>

332
00:19:10.620 --> 00:19:12.734
[newsreader] <i>Superintendent
Verity Pound speaking there</i>

333
00:19:12.758 --> 00:19:14.758
<i>on behalf of the Bristol
Metropolitan Police</i>

334
00:19:14.862 --> 00:19:18.310
<i>about the corpse that was
found earlier this afternoon.</i>

335
00:19:18.413 --> 00:19:19.693
<i>This is the news that a body has</i>

336
00:19:19.793 --> 00:19:21.793
<i>been recovered
at St Jordan's church...</i>

337
00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:24.724
<i>Police believe
the victim may have been</i>

338
00:19:24.827 --> 00:19:26.620
<i>concealed after death. and...</i>

339
00:19:26.724 --> 00:19:28.620
[newsreader
continues indistinctly]

340
00:19:31.724 --> 00:19:32.931
[door closes loudly]

341
00:19:33.655 --> 00:19:35.034
[footsteps approaching]

342
00:19:38.655 --> 00:19:40.103
♪ Suspenseful music

343
00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:51.000
[lighter clicks]

344
00:19:51.103 --> 00:19:52.586
♪ Uneasy music

345
00:20:12.137 --> 00:20:13.655
♪

346
00:20:29.724 --> 00:20:31.517
♪

347
00:20:54.965 --> 00:20:56.344
[woman] <i>Victoria!</i>

348
00:20:56.448 --> 00:20:58.000
[woman screaming]

349
00:21:00.482 --> 00:21:02.862
[screams] <i>Victoria!</i>

350
00:21:02.965 --> 00:21:05.034
[screaming] <i>Victoria!</i>

351
00:21:05.241 --> 00:21:06.517
[scream echoes]

352
00:21:06.620 --> 00:21:08.137
[crow caws]

353
00:21:08.241 --> 00:21:10.310
[thunder rumbling]

354
00:21:10.413 --> 00:21:11.655
[rain pattering]

355
00:21:25.965 --> 00:21:27.448
[inhales sharply]

356
00:21:46.793 --> 00:21:48.000
[whimpers]

357
00:21:48.413 --> 00:21:49.413
[crows cawing]

358
00:21:49.448 --> 00:21:50.689
♪ Sombre music

359
00:22:27.448 --> 00:22:32.551
[breathes deeply]

360
00:22:38.172 --> 00:22:39.689
♪

361
00:22:40.793 --> 00:22:42.172
[crows cawing]

362
00:22:46.034 --> 00:22:47.620
[siren wailing]

363
00:22:48.551 --> 00:22:49.631
[Mike] You in a bad mood today?

364
00:22:49.655 --> 00:22:50.896
No. not really. Mike.

365
00:22:51.000 --> 00:22:52.689
Yesterday was
a complete shitshow.

366
00:22:52.793 --> 00:22:54.172
so. yeah. yeah. you're right.

367
00:22:54.275 --> 00:22:55.389
I lost my cool a little bit.

368
00:22:55.413 --> 00:22:57.148
But we're here now. so
let's just forget about it.

369
00:22:57.172 --> 00:22:58.344
-[Mike] Hmm.
-Hey.

370
00:22:58.448 --> 00:22:59.808
-All right?
-You all right. mate?

371
00:23:00.310 --> 00:23:01.458
[Eva] We're still working
our way through

372
00:23:01.482 --> 00:23:02.793
the bodies from the freezers.

373
00:23:02.896 --> 00:23:05.034
but tox has come back
on the first three

374
00:23:05.586 --> 00:23:08.103
and Lidocaine is confirmed
in all of them.

375
00:23:08.827 --> 00:23:09.827
Okay. cheers. pal.

376
00:23:11.103 --> 00:23:13.862
Now. our man Dwyer.
he's a different matter.

377
00:23:14.413 --> 00:23:18.000
His tox has come back negative
for any painkillers.

378
00:23:18.103 --> 00:23:21.275
erm. recreational drugs.
alcohol. et cetera. et cetera.

379
00:23:21.379 --> 00:23:22.482
He's totally clean.

380
00:23:23.586 --> 00:23:25.482
No Lidocaine in him. crucially.

381
00:23:25.758 --> 00:23:27.038
So he would have
felt everything.

382
00:23:28.241 --> 00:23:29.275
Everything.

383
00:23:30.344 --> 00:23:31.344
You ready to take a look?

384
00:23:31.448 --> 00:23:32.551
Yeah. show me the way.

385
00:23:32.655 --> 00:23:34.068
-Er. Mike?
-Yeah?

386
00:23:34.896 --> 00:23:36.586
Have you done
one of these before?

387
00:23:36.689 --> 00:23:38.620
Er...[stutters] not a PM.

388
00:23:38.724 --> 00:23:42.206
Er...[stammers]
I'll just hang back.

389
00:23:42.310 --> 00:23:44.070
-If it's okay.
-Mike. it's fine. it's fine.

390
00:23:47.034 --> 00:23:48.354
-[Eva] Straight ahead.
-[groans]

391
00:23:48.413 --> 00:23:49.773
Dwyer's in
the bottom right drawer.

392
00:23:51.896 --> 00:23:54.551
[Jeanette] So. you're saying
someone wanted him to suffer?

393
00:23:54.655 --> 00:23:56.724
[Eva] Yeah. he'd have felt
absolutely everything.

394
00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:01.034
-You all right?
-Mm.

395
00:24:05.482 --> 00:24:06.896
♪ Suspenseful music

396
00:24:08.000 --> 00:24:09.034
[exhales]

397
00:24:11.206 --> 00:24:13.206
[Eva] Okay. so. as you can see.

398
00:24:13.310 --> 00:24:15.517
he's received a blow
to the back of the head.

399
00:24:15.620 --> 00:24:17.379
-[Mike] Eva?
-Yeah?

400
00:24:19.620 --> 00:24:21.241
Are these items from
Madeleine Burkeman?

401
00:24:21.344 --> 00:24:22.517
[Eva] Er. no.

402
00:24:22.620 --> 00:24:25.448
They're from the body we called
in from St Jordan's Church.

403
00:24:25.931 --> 00:24:27.251
[Mike] Could you run us
through the PM?

404
00:24:27.275 --> 00:24:29.715
-[Jeanette] What is it. Mike?
-Come and have a look at this.

405
00:24:31.827 --> 00:24:32.827
What is it?

406
00:24:36.586 --> 00:24:37.724
What's this. Eva?

407
00:24:38.586 --> 00:24:41.827
Er. this was all on the body
they brought in from the crypt.

408
00:24:41.931 --> 00:24:43.137
Okay. Mike. can you...

409
00:24:43.241 --> 00:24:44.562
[stammers] What am I
looking at. Mike?

410
00:24:44.586 --> 00:24:45.866
Look at the logo on the receipt.

411
00:24:46.517 --> 00:24:47.862
Logo on the receipt.

412
00:24:50.793 --> 00:24:52.000
"Beecham College."

413
00:24:52.965 --> 00:24:54.551
Oh. well bloody done. Mike.

414
00:24:54.655 --> 00:24:56.275
We're gonna need
to see this body.

415
00:24:56.827 --> 00:24:57.838
-[Eva stutters]
-Yeah. there's a...

416
00:24:57.862 --> 00:24:59.413
there's a high chance
it's one of ours.

417
00:25:01.551 --> 00:25:02.655
Oh. well done. Mike.

418
00:25:02.758 --> 00:25:04.158
-Well done. Well done!
-[chuckles]

419
00:25:08.896 --> 00:25:09.896
[Eva sighs]

420
00:25:10.724 --> 00:25:11.804
This is like that nightmare

421
00:25:11.896 --> 00:25:14.206
when you've got a test
that you haven't revised for.

422
00:25:14.310 --> 00:25:16.310
And I haven't written up
anything formally. yet.

423
00:25:16.551 --> 00:25:17.551
It's fine.

424
00:25:19.344 --> 00:25:20.551
Okay.

425
00:25:20.655 --> 00:25:24.724
So. er. we have
a young female here.

426
00:25:25.517 --> 00:25:26.965
I'd age her...

427
00:25:28.344 --> 00:25:30.724
somewhere between 14 and 18

428
00:25:30.827 --> 00:25:32.586
going from the pelvic fusion.

429
00:25:33.448 --> 00:25:36.689
Due to the conditions
in which she was entombed.

430
00:25:36.793 --> 00:25:38.965
a lot of the tissue
has decomposed.

431
00:25:39.068 --> 00:25:41.896
But the head. neck.
torso. the right arm...

432
00:25:43.206 --> 00:25:44.366
that's pretty well preserved.

433
00:25:45.862 --> 00:25:46.896
Cause of death?

434
00:25:47.724 --> 00:25:49.103
Believe it or not. drowning.

435
00:25:51.655 --> 00:25:53.000
So she was placed?

436
00:25:53.103 --> 00:25:55.103
Yeah. There's marks. too.

437
00:25:57.724 --> 00:25:58.965
Where she's been dragged.

438
00:25:59.551 --> 00:26:03.862
No external signs of injury
or blunt force trauma.

439
00:26:03.965 --> 00:26:06.758
We've sent her liver off to tox.

440
00:26:06.862 --> 00:26:08.379
And the dirt

441
00:26:09.551 --> 00:26:11.310
that we found
under her fingernails.

442
00:26:11.413 --> 00:26:12.413
that's silt.

443
00:26:13.931 --> 00:26:17.034
Plus there's plant matter
in her hair. in her throat.

444
00:26:17.137 --> 00:26:18.862
Diatoms in her lungs.
which. okay.

445
00:26:18.965 --> 00:26:20.482
that could be for
a myriad of reasons.

446
00:26:20.586 --> 00:26:21.965
But marry that with the above.

447
00:26:22.655 --> 00:26:24.517
and I'd wager she
drowned in fresh water.

448
00:26:26.034 --> 00:26:27.620
How long was she in the crypt?

449
00:26:27.724 --> 00:26:29.482
Now that's the interesting part.

450
00:26:30.241 --> 00:26:31.344
Excuse me.

451
00:26:32.413 --> 00:26:34.206
See these? They're fillings.

452
00:26:34.758 --> 00:26:36.310
But they're dental amalgam.

453
00:26:36.413 --> 00:26:37.655
Christ. I've got one of them.

454
00:26:37.758 --> 00:26:40.379
Yeah. well. you could be
entitled to compensation.

455
00:26:40.965 --> 00:26:42.000
It's a joke.

456
00:26:42.103 --> 00:26:43.872
It's just they're not
particularly used anymore.

457
00:26:43.896 --> 00:26:45.034
I mean. they're vintage.

458
00:26:45.137 --> 00:26:47.206
And if we take
the attrition into account.

459
00:26:47.758 --> 00:26:50.206
then...[sighs] I'd say...

460
00:26:50.724 --> 00:26:52.724
late '90s. early noughties.

461
00:26:58.137 --> 00:26:59.941
[Jeanette] <i>That body's directly
connected to this case.</i>

462
00:26:59.965 --> 00:27:01.424
We'll have to get
Peter Drake back in.

463
00:27:01.448 --> 00:27:02.551
Maybe the fucker'll talk.

464
00:27:02.655 --> 00:27:04.241
now that another
body's turned up.

465
00:27:04.344 --> 00:27:06.251
We need to get his prints
to add to the database.

466
00:27:06.275 --> 00:27:07.995
Uh-huh. prints.
Er. you got Sophia's. right?

467
00:27:08.034 --> 00:27:09.034
-[sighs]
-Jeanette.

468
00:27:09.103 --> 00:27:10.827
-Sorry. I forgot.
-I'll call her.

469
00:27:10.931 --> 00:27:12.079
-Don't worry about it. I will...
-No. I'll message her.

470
00:27:12.103 --> 00:27:13.251
-You might forget again.
-I'm not...

471
00:27:13.275 --> 00:27:14.793
-[knocks on door]
-[Verity] Come in.

472
00:27:15.482 --> 00:27:16.482
Hang on a minute.

473
00:27:17.172 --> 00:27:18.941
I... I won't stop. I just
thought you should know

474
00:27:18.965 --> 00:27:21.068
that the body that was found
at St Jordan's Church.

475
00:27:21.172 --> 00:27:22.172
it's one of ours.

476
00:27:22.758 --> 00:27:23.758
Jeanette. are you mad?

477
00:27:24.655 --> 00:27:26.758
Look. she went
to Beecham College.

478
00:27:26.862 --> 00:27:28.344
probably the same time
as Victoria.

479
00:27:28.448 --> 00:27:29.517
I mean. she's...

480
00:27:29.862 --> 00:27:31.320
she's one of ours. Verity.
I promise you.

481
00:27:31.344 --> 00:27:33.079
You want me to solve this?
Let me go and solve it. please.

482
00:27:33.103 --> 00:27:35.103
-And what if she isn't?
-Then I'll give her back.

483
00:27:35.896 --> 00:27:36.965
[mouthing] Go away.

484
00:27:37.827 --> 00:27:39.103
Sorry. go on.

485
00:27:40.724 --> 00:27:43.034
-[bell tolling]
-[crow cawing]

486
00:27:47.241 --> 00:27:48.758
Mr Drake in today?

487
00:27:48.862 --> 00:27:49.965
[woman] What do you need?

488
00:27:50.068 --> 00:27:51.344
I wanna speak with him.

489
00:27:51.448 --> 00:27:53.724
No. he. erm... It's Sunday.

490
00:27:53.827 --> 00:27:56.931
He goes home after service
on a Sunday.

491
00:27:57.482 --> 00:28:00.482
Can you tell him
that I called for him?

492
00:28:00.586 --> 00:28:01.724
It's urgent.

493
00:28:02.620 --> 00:28:04.620
-Of course.
-Hmm. Thank you.

494
00:28:05.275 --> 00:28:07.675
Would you keep a record if any
of your students went missing?

495
00:28:08.275 --> 00:28:09.689
Missing?

496
00:28:09.793 --> 00:28:11.896
Oh. er. I mean. I've been here
near on ten years

497
00:28:12.000 --> 00:28:14.000
and no one's gone missing
to my knowledge.

498
00:28:14.103 --> 00:28:15.275
No missing girls?

499
00:28:16.034 --> 00:28:19.413
Around. erm. the late '90s.
early noughties?

500
00:28:19.862 --> 00:28:20.862
Gosh. no!

501
00:28:22.551 --> 00:28:24.310
Do you keep any records
of former students?

502
00:28:24.931 --> 00:28:26.068
[stammers] We... Yes.

503
00:28:26.172 --> 00:28:27.972
But it all depends on
what you're looking for.

504
00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:30.482
I'm... I'd love a list of
all your female students

505
00:28:30.586 --> 00:28:33.379
from mid-'90s to 2005?

506
00:28:33.482 --> 00:28:35.793
Absolutely. Yes.
I... I can email it to you?

507
00:28:35.896 --> 00:28:38.137
Yep. That's great.

508
00:28:38.620 --> 00:28:39.724
Cheers.

509
00:28:40.517 --> 00:28:41.517
Thank you.

510
00:28:43.034 --> 00:28:44.310
[keyboard clacking]

511
00:28:47.551 --> 00:28:49.111
Are the bursary recipients
on that list?

512
00:28:49.758 --> 00:28:52.137
